<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>7-2071.12</num>
  <heading>Funding for the Ombudsman Program.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>Funding sources for the Ombudsman Program shall include:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>District local appropriations; and</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>Medicaid federal matching funds.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>Nothing in this chapter shall prohibit a corporation, organization, or consortia of organizations selected to operate the Health Care Ombudsman Program from raising private money through foundation resources to supplement government funds for the program.</text>
  </para>
